> Our break from sandwiches is officially over. News flash: This sandwich loaded with rich flavors and textures will make you swoon all over again!

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.

== Crispy Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Halve @lemon{1}. Halve @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pickled Shallot Green Salad ==

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine shallot, juice from half the lemon, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, 1 tsp water, salt, and pepper. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}; microwave for ~{1%minute}. Set aside to pickle.

In a separate #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon} with @roasted onion & garlic spread{1%ounce}. Season with @salt{to taste} to taste.

== Steak & Eggs ==

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

While steak cooks, toast baguettes until golden.

Once steak is cooked to desired doneness, turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. Fry eggs to preference. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

== Salad Dressing ==

Remove pickled shallot from pickling liquid (reserve liquid).

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together reserved shallot pickling liquid, @dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, and @olive oil{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add @mixed greens{2%ounce} and pickled shallot to bowl; toss to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Assembly ==

Slice steak against the grain.

Spread garlic herb butter over bottom baguette halves; spread half the roasted garlic aioli over top baguette halves. Fill baguettes with steak, eggs, and a bit of salad; close sandwiches.

Divide sandwiches, potatoes, and remaining salad between plates. Serve with remaining roasted garlic aioli on the side for dipping.